column5: Big flows, big fish.  Best fish of the fall! (yet)
the story i could have told you about the two brown a rainbow and a salmon.  could not hook for love of god.
Love the colours in that pic, Doc....nicely done!
That fish was quite the handful.  I got my cardio for the week chasing it downstream in the high flows...
Awesome colors on that bow Thanks for sharing Dr S!!! Leechman

Nice fish and clours! All the bows I landed in September were big.  Nothing small.  Seems like those dry years coughed up little recruitment.  The water levels have come down quite a bit from late September?  Would you say the run is half way through or almost done? There is a slight chance I might make it up there Nov 20th.
Love those fall colours. Great stuff doc!
Buck, that's not a buck. It's a fish. Looks like a spawning Rainbow to me. Nice Rainbow Trout.
